                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/215</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-21T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram of April 20, 11 p.m. The loan is a provincial obligation guaranteed
                    by the Chinese Government, a form which has advantage of gaining direct
                    provincial support and security in addition to that of Central Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
